GemFind.net, the jewelry industry’s one-stop shopping destination for business-to-business online solutions, such as web development and execution, online advertising and marketing, virtual jewelry and diamond inventory from hundreds of designers/manufacturers and diamond dealers with many online tools as well.

Alex Fetanat successfully led ACS for 6 years until it was sold in 1994. That very same year, Alex started a Website hosting and development company, which he sold two years later.

In terms of education, Alex Fetanat earned his degree in computer engineering from California State University, Fullerton in 1987.

GemFind is a delighted member of the American Gem Society in addition to CJA, AGTA, JIC, 24 kt club and other jewelry associations. He was recommended for the Entrepreneur of the Year award in February 2009 by Orange County Business Journal.
